Hi everyone
As you would have seen in the media, it’s been a good week in relation to the number of new cases of Covid-19 in our community. We have now commenced checking temperatures for one client, and completed our first patient transfer. Thanks so much for those of you who have been willing to assist in these and other tasks over the last two weeks, and to Stephanie and team who have been working tirelessly behind the scenes on the logistics.
Our community care program continues to practically support very vulnerable communities, and I’m pleased that we have received some extra funding through SA Health to assist with this work. Thank you to our community care volunteers who continue to provide such a vital service.
The weekend we take some time out to reflect on the selfless service by so many as we acknowledge Anzac Day. As I write this, I should be in attendance at one of the many Anzac Eve Youth Vigils occurring in Adelaide. Having been involved in these in my previous role in the CFS and SES, I know the value of the youth vigil and look forward to next year’s event.

St John was ably represented by Unley cadet Olivia Stead along with young people from other cadet organisations. A big thanks to Olivia for representing St John so well – and also to Samuel Shepherd and Vince Scotland who are both involved in the vigil as well.
Have a restful and reflective day tomorrow, and feel free to reach out to me anytime.
Cheers
Mark

"Jong Un Eating a Corndog" is a much discussed concept on /jp/. The significance of it is disputed, so I will focus on one core concept: the symbolism behind it. But first we must identify and explore the key components of it. Hinanawi Jong Un is a human child that has ascended to become a celestial being. In Hinduism, she would be called a Siddha or a Deva. In Chinese, it would be refered to as a Tian Xian, or heavenly immortal. In Japanese, it would be using the same kanji characters as in Chinese, being called a Tennin. She is also refered to as an angel, although the role of a heavenly messenger is better suited to her companion Nagae Iku. Regardless of which Oriental cosmology she claims the greatest influence from, Hinanawi Jong Un in Touhou: Scarlet Weather Rhapsody is presented as a roving celestial being that decides to cause mayhem out of childish boredom. A corndog on the other hand is simply a sausage coated in a thick layer of cornmeal batter on a stick. It is considered a quintessential part of the American diet, being a cheap combination between convenience and an arguably delicious meal of protein and carbohydrates. It is not a new concept by any means, but it is something that is also unmistakably modern and mundane. Thus this is why "Jong Un Eating a Corndog" is so intriguing. Why exactly is a celestial being consuming a corndog, despite having access to the Jade Wine Waterfalls and Immortal Peach Orchards of Heaven?

Jong Un is shown to represent infinity, as she to is of the sky. As to the corndog to her, the Route 66 sign is to the sky. What of the tiny stretch of road to the vastness of the heavens? Not out of pleasure, as we can see from her expression, but of necessity to understand the realm she observes from up high.
